    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Are you doing this for security, or to avoid confusing users?\n\nIf you want to avoid confusion, you can turn off automagics by setting `c.InteractiveShell.automagic = False` in a config file. This will prevent `ls` from working, but you'll still be able to achieve the same thing with `!ls`, or `os.system('ls')`, or `os.listdir()`.\n\nIf you want to restrict what users can do, that's much harder. The best bet is to run the kernel in some sort of container, and let users do whatever they want within the container.\n"
